# MMO001 Workflow

## Before implementation

1. Read [TODO.md](../../TODO.md) and identify the **next unchecked item**
2. Summarize scope and approach before coding (plan mode or brief outline)
3. Mark the item in progress; do not start unrelated work

## Git branches

- One feature per branch from `main`: `feature/<short-kebab-name>`
- Examples: `feature/click-to-move`, `feature/mouse-aim`, `feature/monster-combat`
- Merge to `main` only when the feature is complete, **`npm test` passes**, and smoke-tested
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials)

## GitHub remote

- **Remote:** `origin` → `https://github.com/wanglen/mmo001.git`
- **Repository:** [wanglen/mmo001](https://github.com/wanglen/mmo001)
- `main` tracks `origin/main`; pull before starting a new feature if the remote may be ahead
- Commit and push: `./scripts/commit-and-push.sh "..."` — on `main`, pushes `main`; on a feature branch, merges into `main` then pushes (only when the user asks)
- Manual alternative: commit on the feature branch, `git checkout main && git merge feature/<name>`, then `git push origin main`
- Open PRs with `gh pr create` when the user asks; do not push or open PRs proactively
- Never `git push --force` to `main`

## Merge on user approval

When the user **approves** the work (e.g. "approve", "looks good", "merge it", "LGTM", or approving a merge to `main`), **merge to `main` without asking again**.

### Pre-merge checklist

1. `npm test` passes
2. Version, CHANGELOG, README, and TODO are updated if behavior changed
3. All feature changes are **committed** on the feature branch (use `./scripts/commit-and-push.sh "..."` when the user asked to commit and push)

### Merge steps

```bash
git checkout main
git merge feature/<branch-name>
```

- Use fast-forward when possible; otherwise a merge commit is fine
- Stay on `main` after merge; report the merge commit hash
- Do **not** merge without explicit user approval
- Do **not** push to remote unless the user asks

### After merge

- Push `main` to GitHub when the user asks: `git push origin main` or `./scripts/commit-and-push.sh "..."` on `main`
- Optionally create the next `feature/<name>` branch from `main` if continuing the roadmap

## Versioning (each merged feature)

1. Bump `version` in [package.json](../../package.json) (semver: patch/minor by scope)
2. Move [CHANGELOG.md](../../CHANGELOG.md) `[Unreleased]` entries into a dated version section
3. Update [README.md](../../README.md) if behavior, setup, or controls changed
4. Check off the completed item in [TODO.md](../../TODO.md)

## Commit and push

When the user wants changes **committed and pushed**:

```bash
./scripts/commit-and-push.sh "Imperative message focusing on why"
```

Runs `npm test` by default; use `SKIP_TESTS=1` for docs-only. On a feature branch, merges into `main` before pushing. For **commit without push**, use manual git — this script always pushes `main`.

## Commit messages

- Imperative mood, 1–2 sentences focusing on **why**
- Example: `Add click-to-move with A* pathfinding`

## Module layout

Follow [.cursor/rules/architecture.mdc](architecture.mdc). Summary:

- `server/app/` — bootstrap, plugin registry, event bus, game loop
- `server/entities/` — players, monsters, loot, NPCs
- `server/plugins/<feature>/` — socket handlers, bus subscribers, serialization slices
- `public/js/app/` + `public/js/plugins/` — client plugin host and feature UI
- `public/js/core/` — loop, input router, camera (not feature-specific)
- `shared/plugins/` + `shared/content/` — pure domain logic and JSON data packs
- Legacy paths (`server/systems/`, `server/players/`) are re-export stubs only — import canonical paths
